<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 04 at 11:10PM CDT until May 04 at 11:45PM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1145 PM CDT
FOR CENTRAL MONTAGUE COUNTY...
At 1110 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Nocona, moving
northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Nocona and Stoneburg.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for north central
Texas.</instruction>
